result.execSummary:
Michael D. Booker was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Michael D. Booker was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Signed waiver of extradition by defendant and judge.

Defendant Michael D. Booker by video, in custody with attorney Amanda K. Riek.  Jane E. Kohlwey appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendants rights were recited.  Defendant signed extradition waiver.  Sheriffs Dept. to bring waiver over for Judges signature.

Defendant Michael D. Booker in court, in custody by video.  Jordan Lippert appeared for the State of Wisconsin. defendant acknowledges complaint, matter to be continued until tomorrow at 2:00 P.M. on 8/5/14  Extradition hearing scheduled for August 5, 2014 at 02:00 pm.
